# ML Model Management Standards

## Model File Organization

- **Production models**: Root `models/` directory (versioned, source-controlled)
- **Uploaded models**: `agent/model_storage/` directory (discovered automatically)
- User-uploaded models: `agent/model_storage/custom/`
- Model-specific directories: `agent/model_storage/xgboost/`, `agent/model_storage/lstm/`, etc.

## Environment Variables

- `MODEL_PATH`: Points to specific production model file (e.g., `models/xgboost_BTCUSD_15m.pkl`)
- `MODEL_DIR`: Points to directory for model discovery (e.g., `./agent/model_storage`)

## Model Implementation

All models must implement `MCPModelNode` interface:
- Predictions normalized to -1.0 to +1.0 range
- Human-readable reasoning/explanations
- Confidence scores
- Feature importance tracking

## Model Metadata

**Required Fields**:
- `model_name`: Unique identifier
- `model_type`: Model type (xgboost, lstm, transformer, etc.)
- `version`: Semantic version (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH)
- `features_required`: List of required feature names
- `description`: Model description

## Model Versioning

- Use semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH)
- Keep old versions for rollback capability
- Document version changes in metadata
- Test new versions before activation
